abstract: Pete Buttigieg was just hours removed from his strong showing in Iowa when he confronted a question about whether it would last.
snippet: Pete Buttigieg was just hours removed from his strong showing in Iowa when he confronted a question about whether it would last.
lead_paragraph: CONCORD, N.H. — Pete Buttigieg was just hours removed from his strong showing in Iowa when he confronted a question about whether it would last.
headline_main: Buttigieg Faces New Urgency in Bid to Win Minority Voters
headline_print_headline: Buttigieg Faces New Urgency in Bid to Win Minority Voters

abstract: They said what was, essentially, the only thing they could say: “Voters, please do what the Senate didn’t.”
snippet: They said what was, essentially, the only thing they could say: “Voters, please do what the Senate didn’t.”
lead_paragraph: The Democratic presidential candidates have been responding this afternoon to the thing they all knew was coming: the Senate’s acquittal of President Trump. And they all said what was, essentially, the only thing they could say: “Voters, please do what the Senate didn’t.”

abstract: President Donald Trump was gone, the House lights were dimming, and House Speaker Nancy Pelosi looked up to her friends and family in the gallery overhead.  She held up the speech she had shredded behind Trump's back, on live television. She put her hand to her heart, dipped her head and gave a little bow.
snippet: President Donald Trump was gone, the House lights were dimming, and House Speaker Nancy Pelosi looked up to her friends and family in the gallery overhead.  She held up the speech she had shredded behind Trump's back, on live television. She put h...
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — President Donald Trump was gone, the House lights were dimming, and House Speaker Nancy Pelosi looked up to her friends and family in the gallery overhead. She held up the speech she had shredded behind Trump's back, on live television. She put her hand to her heart, dipped her head and gave a little bow.
headline_main: Impeachment Done, Pelosi Unburdens Herself About Trump
headline_print_headline: Impeachment Done, Pelosi Unburdens Herself About Trump

abstract: As Republicans rallied behind President Trump, Senator Mitt Romney of Utah, the party’s 2012 presidential nominee, joined Democrats in voting to convict, the only senator to cross party lines.
snippet: As Republicans rallied behind President Trump, Senator Mitt Romney of Utah, the party’s 2012 presidential nominee, joined Democrats in voting to convict, the only senator to cross party lines.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — After five months of hearings, investigations and revelations about President Trump’s dealings with Ukraine, a divided United States Senate acquitted him on Wednesday of charges that he abused his power and obstructed Congress to aid his own re-election, bringing an acrimonious impeachment trial to its expected end.

abstract: The chairman of the Democratic National Committee called on Thursday for a “recanvass” of the results of Monday's Iowa caucus, which was marred by technical problems and delays.
snippet: The chairman of the Democratic National Committee called on Thursday for a “recanvass” of the results of Monday's Iowa caucus, which was marred by technical problems and delays.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The chairman of the Democratic National Committee called on Thursday for a “recanvass” of the results of Monday's Iowa caucus, which was marred by technical problems and delays.
headline_main: DNC Calls for a 'Recanvass' of Iowa Results After Delays
headline_print_headline: DNC Calls for a 'Recanvass' of Iowa Results After Delays

abstract: Black lawmakers in South Carolina are calling on former Vice President Joe Biden to disavow statements from a longtime friend and campaign surrogate that they say are racist.
snippet: Black lawmakers in South Carolina are calling on former Vice President Joe Biden to disavow statements from a longtime friend and campaign surrogate that they say are racist.
lead_paragraph: COLUMBIA, S.C. — Black lawmakers in South Carolina are calling on former Vice President Joe Biden to disavow statements from a longtime friend and campaign surrogate that they say are racist.
headline_main: Black Lawmakers Demand Biden Disavow Surrogate's Comments
headline_print_headline: Black Lawmakers Demand Biden Disavow Surrogate's Comments

abstract: Democrats refuse to talk about how his failure to deliver major changes may have fed voter disaffection in 2016.
snippet: Democrats refuse to talk about how his failure to deliver major changes may have fed voter disaffection in 2016.
lead_paragraph: The sting of Hillary Clinton’s defeat in 2016 still hangs heavy over the Democratic Party. There has yet to emerge a consensus understanding of the party’s failure to beat an opponent who almost everyone assumed could be defeated. Some have focused on voter suppression, others on Russian interference. Mrs. Clinton continues to blame Bernie Sanders. But missing from the various theories is how Barack Obama’s tenure may also have contributed to voter disaffection because he failed to bring about the transformational changes he promised.
